  {
    "S.No.": 10,
    "SourceprojectName": "East Africa_PRD_2025",
    "Ticketid": "CQR-00000198223",
    "Subject": "Duplication of Transactions",
    "ReportedByEmailId": "Tito.Rutto@equitybank.co.ke",
    "ReportingTime": "05-Mar-2026 20:12:28",
    "CurrentStatus": "Exit",
    "Customername": "Equity Bank Kenya Limited",
    "Problem Type (Customer)": "Defect",
    "Problem Type (Newgen)": "Defect",
    "UserEnvironmentType": "Production",
    "NewgenEnvironmentType": "Production",
    "ProjectName": "East Africa_PRD_2025",
    "ModuleName": "",
    "NewgenSeverity": "S2",
    "Customer Priority": "High",
    "TicketRelatedTo": "System Partially Down",
    "FirstResponseTime": "06-Mar-2026 12:18:53",
    "ClosingDate": "06-Mar-2026 18:03:00",
    "RaiseDispute": "",
    "TicketReopenFlag": false,
    "TicketTransferflag": "FALSE",
    "TransferDate": "",
    "Response_outofsla": "06-Mar-2026 20:11:28",
    "Resolution_outofsla": "10-Mar-2026 16:25:28",
    "Response_TicketSLAMet": "Yes",
    "Resolution_TicketSLAMet": "Yes",
    "GoldCustomer": "No",
    "CustomerSLAType": "Response + Resolution",
    "Support_Scope": "Business Hours",
    "L1Analysis": "",
    "AssigntoUserName": "aman.aashish.singh",
    "ResolutionComment": "1. Duplication of Outgoing Messages Duplicate outward messages attachment to WI were observed  Analysis: When the user initially clicked the Book Transaction button and received the response, they did not properly close the WorkItem. As a result, the WorkItem did not route to the Exit WorkStep as expected. Later, another user opened the same WorkItem and processed the transaction again, which caused the generated message to be attached twice.Resolution: Advise users to close WorkItems properly. This concern was raised and addressed previously as well.\n 2. Duplication of Incoming Transactions Single incoming transactions generated two transaction IDs, resulting in double crediting in Finacle. \n Analysis: When the STP_BookTransaction Utility tried to post the transaction got the Null response from the Finacle/OMNI, so the WorkItem get routed to the Checker WorkStep. But the the posting call done by STP_BookTransaction Utility processed the tranaction from the Finacle Backend. This causes the posting twice.Resolution : This issue is with finacle/OMNI side. \n3. Transaction Posting Failures (Unlien Error) Some transactions failed to post due to the below error: Sorry, we could not unlien your account despite liens already having been lifted in Finacle.Analysis: During the ERP integration deployment (UG, RW, TZ), an unapproved line of code was introduced, which was not part of the release build. This caused the unLien to fail.Resolution: After removing that line of code redeploying",
    "Newgen Issue Sub Category": "Custom Code Issue"
  },
